      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial legal tool that protects fundamental rights against government overreach, ensuring that the government cannot infringe upon deeply rooted liberties. This concept has been vital in expanding civil rights by striking down laws that infringe on personal autonomy, such as those concerning marriage or bodily integrity. It serves as a bulwark against majoritarian tyranny, safeguarding individual freedoms that the majority might otherwise suppress.",
      "source": "target",
